                            <comment id="10949" author="eneko.alonso@gmail.com" created="Mon, 29 Aug 2016 01:08:25 -0400"  >&lt;p&gt;The following URL returns no results. My take is that the project is not open to the public nor to signed up users.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://jira.perfect.org:8080/projects/ISS/issues&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://jira.perfect.org:8080/projects/ISS/issues&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Url was found here: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/PerfectlySoft/Perfect-Redis&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://github.com/PerfectlySoft/Perfect-Redis&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Despite that url, sign in up on JIRA provides no access to any list of open issues.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="10950" author="eneko.alonso@gmail.com" created="Mon, 29 Aug 2016 01:10:11 -0400"  >&lt;p&gt;Seems like currently users can only access their own submitted issues which prevents any type of collaboration.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Issues should be publicly accessible, indexable by Google and any signed up user should be able to comment on them.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="10951" author="jono" created="Mon, 29 Aug 2016 09:55:39 -0400"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Eneko Alonso,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For some reason the addition of new users to the Jira-Service-Desk group was not happening. This has now been resolved.&lt;br/&gt;
Thanks for bringing this to our attention Eneko!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#8211; Jonathan Guthrie&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="10952" author="eneko.alonso@gmail.com" created="Mon, 29 Aug 2016 15:10:27 -0400"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Jonathan,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I just logged back in and still can only see my issues (this one). I&apos;m sure there are other open/closed issues.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Regards,&lt;br/&gt;
Eneko&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="10953" author="eneko.alonso@gmail.com" created="Mon, 29 Aug 2016 15:12:48 -0400"  >&lt;p&gt;Never mind, that applies only to the Service Desk url: &lt;a href=&quot;http://jira.perfect.org:8080/servicedesk/customer/portal/1&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://jira.perfect.org:8080/servicedesk/customer/portal/1&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A bit confusing, I would say. Not sure the service desk is worth it, if users must log in to submit issues/requests, why not have them do it directly on the JIRA project?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
